<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="37" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[824,1474,1562,1651]" pageId="4" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis box="[862,968,1562,1586]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="37">Phenology</emphasis>
. – Flowers were observed in May and also in November-December (in cultivation). Fruits were registered reaching maturity in May and February (in cultivation).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="37" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="4.[824,1474,1690,1938]" pageId="4" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis box="[862,1051,1691,1714]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="37">Conservation status</emphasis>
. – The new species has been observed and collected in a single locality, i.e. EOO &lt;
<quantity box="[1227,1304,1722,1746]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" unit="km" value="100.0">100 km</quantity>
², and AAO &lt;
<quantity metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" unit="km" value="10.0">10 km</quantity>
² along an unpaved road. Projects of improving and paving this section of road ES-379 were scheduled in 2014. Nevertheless, those projects seem so far paralyzed. Therefore, the locality remains strongly at risk of being destroyed. 
<taxonomicName authority="statusLabelOccurrence" authorityName="Chautems &amp; Valquíria F. Dutra &amp; Fontana &amp; Peixoto &amp; Perret &amp; Rossini" authorityYear="2019" box="[1273,1451,1850,1874]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Sinningia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hoehnei">
<emphasis box="[1273,1451,1850,1874]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="37">Sinningia hoehnei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is assigned a preliminary assessment as “Critically Endangered” [CR B2ab(iii)] using the IUCN Red List (
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN" box="[1269,1405,1914,1938]" journalOrPublisher="IUCN Species Survival Commission, IUCN, Gland &amp; Cambridge" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" refId="ref5335" refString="IUCN (2012). IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria: Version 3.1 ed. 2. IUCN Species Survival Commission, IUCN, Gland &amp; Cambridge." title="IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria: Version 3.1 ed" type="book" year="2012">IUCN, 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
